NURS 5323 - Holistic Health: The Art and Science of Caring
and Healing
Explores the application of holistic philosophy and theory into practice.
Included will be seminar discussion, demonstration, and experiential
sessions on holistic health assessment and alternative treatment modes to
promote health and healing in practice and daily living. Course projects
include analysis of current and projected trends in the provision of health
care, the role of the informed consumer of health care, comparative
studies of traditional versus alternative medicine, and research based
holistic health care. Open to all majors; graduate status required.
